\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Slight variation of \texttt  {w2.m}: one interior vertex of the $11 \times 11$ reference at $p=4$ is displaced toward a neighbour, creating a sliver cluster. (\subref  {fig:ref-skewed}) Skewed reference with $\max \eta = 4.63$. (\subref  {fig:tangled-skewed}) Boundary on side\nobreakspace  {}4 displaced by $0.5 \sin (\pi y)$, producing heavy tangling near the perturbed edge on top of the reference-induced sliver. (\subref  {fig:smoothed-skewed}) After unmodified Winslow: elements are valid, but the reference skew persists, with $\max \eta = 7.17$ on the sliver in the upper-right.\relax }}{3}{figure.caption.3}\protected@file@percent }
